The  widget abstracts all the complexity of animation for you. It simply transforms the changes—how it does it doesn’t matter. That’s the power of declarative UI.For navigation we user  package which leverages Flutter Router api to provide url based navigation. so as we navigate inside the app, it reflects in the browser address bar and by typing in the address bar it directly shows the target page.add  to your .Create a folder named  and add a file named  . let’s define the routes:enum Routes {
  home(''),
  signInAndSecurity('security'),
  personalInformation('information'),
  paymentMethods('payment'),
  familySharing('family'),
  devices('devices'),
  privacy('privacy');

  const Routes(this.value);
  final String value;
}
These are list of routes or destination the app can navigate.now add below code inside  file:extension MenuItemTypeFromString on MenuItemType {
  static MenuItemType fromString(String value) {
    if (value == Routes.signInAndSecurity.value) {
      return MenuItemType.security;
    } else if (value == Routes.personalInformation.value) {
      return MenuItemType.information;
    } else if (value == Routes.paymentMethods.value) {
      return MenuItemType.payment;
    } else if (value == Routes.familySharing.value) {
      return MenuItemType.family;
    } else if (value == Routes.devices.value) {
      return MenuItemType.devices;
    } else if (value == Routes.privacy.value) {
      return MenuItemType.privacy;
    } else {
      return MenuItemType.security;
    }
  }
}

class AppRouter {
  AppRouter._();

  static final router = GoRouter(
    initialLocation: '/',
    routes: [
      GoRoute(
        path: '/',
        redirect: (context, state) => state.namedLocation(
          Routes.home.value,
          params: {'section': Routes.signInAndSecurity.name},
        ),
      ),
      GoRoute(
        name: Routes.home.value,
        path: '/account/manage/section/:section',
        builder: (context, state) {
          final section = state.params['section']!;
          return HomePage(
            key: state.pageKey,
            tab: MenuItemTypeFromString.fromString(section),
          );
        },
      ),
      // Forwarding routes to avoid passing the section param everywhere.
      GoRoute(
        name: Routes.signInAndSecurity.value,
        path: '/security',
        redirect: (context, state) => state.namedLocation(
          Routes.home.value,
          params: {'section': Routes.signInAndSecurity.name},
        ),
      ),
      GoRoute(
        name: Routes.personalInformation.value,
        path: '/information',
        redirect: (context, state) => state.namedLocation(
          Routes.home.value,
          params: {'section': Routes.personalInformation.name},
        ),
      ),
    ],
  );
}
\
We have defined a list of routes and an initial path, so when you open the app in the browser, it should show the home page. But the default path for the Apple ID dashboard is /account/manage/section/security, so if you look at the first route, you’ll see that we redirect to the correct path.Then we define a route named , which reads the passed route parameters, converts them to the proper , and returns the .Now update the home page side menu with:SideMenu(
  selectedIndex: _selectedIndex,
  onPressed: (index) {
    _selectedIndex = index;
    switch (index) {
      case 0:
        context.goNamed(Routes.signInAndSecurity.name);
        break;
      case 1:
        context.goNamed(Routes.personalInformation.name);
        break;
      case 2:
        context.goNamed(Routes.paymentMethods.name);
        break;
    }
  },
),
\
So here’s how it works: when a side menu item gets tapped, we navigate to a specific tab by passing the target route name. I have separated  from  because they fulfill different purposes—one is for , and the other is for routing—even though I have used almost similar keys.As you can see, we have not used any string comparison. If you mistype a string, the connection is broken, so be careful not to use strings. Instead, use compiler features to catch errors during compile time rather than at runtime.But how does the home page change pages? 🤔One of the common layout widgets in Flutter is IndexedStack, which shows a single child from a list of children. So by selecting an item, we rebuild the home page with the selected tab, and it shows the selected page, which uses internally.Update your  with the following:import 'package:appleid_dashboard/router/routes.dart';
